{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"alias":"enervated-snoozy-needletail","description":"Run the standing discriminates_novelty eval against the plan-review novelty scorer (prompt src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_novelty.md) and record the result: post-flip field data shows 33 remediation-eligible reviews produced ZERO novelty drops, which is consistent either with a healthy precision-first quadrant (novel findings rarely both score >= 0.7 novelty AND < 0.4 priority) or with a silently failing scorer (the fail-safe returns zero drops on error). This task determines which, with evidence, and files the follow-up.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The eval runs to completion: `rebar prompt eval plan-review-novelty` (or the documented equivalent runner surfaced by `rebar prompt eval --help`), from the repo venv, with the command line and full result summary recorded as a comment on this ticket. [operator-attested] The comment includes the exact command, the score/verdict per case, and the run timestamp.\n- [ ] The 33 eligible-but-zero-drop reviews are re-examined against the eval outcome: a one-paragraph conclusion comment states whether the scorer discriminates (and drops were correctly withheld) or the scorer is defective. [operator-attested] The conclusion comment cites at least two concrete sidecar examples by ticket id.\n- [ ] If the scorer is defective, a bug ticket is created and linked discovered_from this task; if healthy, this ticket's conclusion says so and no bug is filed. Oracle: `rebar deps <this-id>` shows the discovered_from link in the defective case.","id":"0730-6ceb-88c3-430c","parent_id":"d195-aeb8-2400-484b","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Run discriminates_novelty eval; determine why zero floor drops; file follow-up"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784085100572163001,"uuid":"2e5ed50f-dcb1-4990-b762-ca75a93da16d"}